        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: read Windsurf Devin session from app origin",
        "body": "## Summary\n- read structured Windsurf/Devin localStorage from `https://app.devin.ai` before the legacy `https://windsurf.com` origin\n- keep `app.devin.ai` and `windsurf.com` values isolated as separate complete session candidates so partial new-origin data cannot poison a legacy fallback bundle\n- preserve the raw LevelDB text-entry scan as an additional isolated fallback candidate after structured origin snapshots, so stale app-origin storage does not hide a working legacy text fallback\n- add importer and fetch-path regression coverage for partial app-origin storage, complete legacy-origin storage, and structured-origin plus text-fallback ordering\n\n## Verification\n- `make check`\n- `git diff --check HEAD^ HEAD`\n- `swift test --filter WindsurfDevinSessionImporterTests --skip-update` was attempted twice on head `037552ca`; both local runs stayed at the Sparkle 2.9.1 SwiftPM binary artifact download step and were terminated before compilation. CI should provide the full Swift build/test signal.\n\nFixes steipete/CodexBar#1564",
